msgid "Eris"
msgstr "Eris"

#: ../../E/Eris.rst:7
msgid "/e´ris/, n\\."
msgstr "/e´ris/, 名詞"

#: ../../E/Eris.rst:9
msgid ""
"The Greek goddess of Chaos, Discord, Confusion, and Things You Know Not Of; "
"her name was latinized to Discordia and she was worshiped by that name in "
"Rome. Not a very friendly deity in the Classical original, she was "
"reinvented as a more benign personification of creative anarchy starting in "
"1959 by the adherents of :ref:`Discordianism` and has since been a semi-"
"serious subject of veneration in several ‘fringe’ cultures, including "
"hackerdom. See :ref:`Discordianism`\\, :ref:`Church-of-the-SubGenius`\\."
msgstr ""
"混沌、不和、混乱、そして汝の知らぬ事どもをつかさどるギリシャの女神。その名はDiscordiaとラテン語化され、ローマではその名で崇拝された。古典の原典ではあまり友好的な神格ではないが、1959年以降、\\"
" :ref:`Discordianism`\\ "
"の信奉者たちによって、より穏やかな創造的アナーキーの擬人化として作り直され、以来ハッカー界を含むいくつかの‘周縁’文化において半ば本気の崇拝対象となっている。\\"
" :ref:`Discordianism`\\ 、\\ :ref:`Church-of-the-SubGenius`\\ を参照。"
